WEBVTT

00:01.980 --> 00:08.280
Shri Devi Puja. Rahuri (Hindistan)
26 Ocak 1984

02:38.900 --> 02:44.860
Rahuri has a special significance in the history of the Goddess,

02:46.030 --> 02:53.940
that when the horrible rakshasa, called Rahu,

02:56.900 --> 03:01.110
started ruling this area and devastating it.

03:02.820 --> 03:07.900
The whole suffered, all the God-fearing people ….

03:09.480 --> 03:14.360
Then the Goddess took Her incarnation

03:15.980 --> 03:20.480
here and She killed this man, this rakshasa

03:22.110 --> 03:24.030
and there are different places

03:24.110 --> 03:27.480
where how he ran, how She caught him

03:27.860 --> 03:32.480
and ultimately killed – he was killed in Rahuri.

03:33.070 --> 03:39.030
And that’s why rahu-ri – “ri” starts from the Hrim,

03:39.940 --> 03:43.110
as you know that: Aim, Klim, Hrim

03:43.480 --> 03:48.110
are the three words denoting the three powers of the Goddess.

03:48.480 --> 03:52.820
Aim, Hrim and Klim: Aim is the Mahakali,

03:54.400 --> 04:00.480
Hrim is the Mahalakshmi and Klim is the Mahasaraswati.

04:01.480 --> 04:06.360
So, with the Hrim-power She killed this rakshasa,

04:06.480 --> 04:10.030
and then – after that killing –

04:10.900 --> 04:13.110
bhaktas started living here.

04:13.900 --> 04:16.280
And a king came all the way from Rajpur,

04:16.480 --> 04:22.480
Rajputana – and started worshipping the Goddess.

04:25.360 --> 04:30.820
And went – he was a poor man, he came here as a poor man –

04:32.360 --> 04:35.820
while worshipping the Goddess

04:38.360 --> 04:41.480
he raised this again into another kingdom,

04:42.320 --> 04:45.360
and that’s why they are called as Shalivahanas

04:45.480 --> 04:48.820
because they carry the shawl of the Goddess.

04:50.360 --> 04:56.150
This Shalivahanas, later on in the dynasty, was a [INDIST., SOUNDS LIKE Bhobruvaha]

04:56.480 --> 04:59.110
who fought with the [INDIST. SOUNDS LIKE Maharaja]

04:59.480 --> 05:02.820
and defeated him, who was from Ujiara [?]. Surprisingly

05:03.230 --> 05:05.900
many of My relations are still in Ujiara

05:06.230 --> 05:08.980
and they are following a new vision.

05:11.110 --> 05:14.110
So because he fought him

05:14.320 --> 05:19.820
and he captured him

05:20.110 --> 05:22.980
many people from here shifted there

05:23.150 --> 05:28.230
and settled down in Ujiara.

05:29.860 --> 05:35.440
Now this Rahuri developed gradually

05:37.820 --> 05:40.900
into a very modern city,

05:41.280 --> 05:44.480
or you can say in a modernized.

05:46.110 --> 05:51.280
And when we go to [INDIST.SOUNDS LIKE Nankhara] you will be able to see it.

05:51.860 --> 05:54.480
The forefathers

05:55.110 --> 05:57.400
of Mine were called as Shalivahanas

05:57.820 --> 06:01.900
and My mother`s place [INDIST.SOUNDS LIKE Rhaduvas] where they resided and lived.

06:02.110 --> 06:05.820
So Rahuri has a special significance

06:06.110 --> 06:09.820
in the life of Sahaja Yoga, or I should say in My own life.

06:10.860 --> 06:15.320
And that is why surprisingly that in Rahuri we have established

06:15.480 --> 06:20.070
our center in the biggest way.

06:20.480 --> 06:23.070
Because the kings here worshipped

06:23.480 --> 06:28.280
the Mother with a shawl.

06:28.940 --> 06:33.820
Now this has a special meaning as the significance

06:34.110 --> 06:36.820
goes, or you can say the symbolic - it is -

06:36.980 --> 06:39.980
it covers the modesty of the Mother.

06:40.980 --> 06:44.480
Mother protects us, She looks after us.

06:45.110 --> 06:47.820
So this is the one which covers Her,

06:48.110 --> 06:51.940
gives Her the grace,

06:52.480 --> 06:56.070
gives Her the protection from the cold

06:56.280 --> 06:59.480
and when the children are suffering,

06:59.900 --> 07:05.110
or are tired, or are sick She covers them with the shawl.

07:06.230 --> 07:09.400
So the shawl has a very big meaning

07:10.280 --> 07:13.230
and because the used to carry the shawl of the Mother

07:13.360 --> 07:15.480
all the time in their hands,

07:15.900 --> 07:18.780
that’s why they are called as Shalivahanas.

07:18.940 --> 07:21.320
So the significance of Rahuri is very great

07:21.480 --> 07:23.480
and you will also see that

07:23.940 --> 07:29.150
in the gross also the people here are very receptive to Sahaja Yoga.

07:29.480 --> 07:35.480
Even the factory people – I went to see them before I came here,

07:35.940 --> 07:38.860
to talk to them. And they are so much submerged

07:39.110 --> 07:41.070
in the developments of Sahaja Yoga

07:41.230 --> 07:43.230
and amount of things they want to do,

07:43.480 --> 07:46.480
and want to take advantage of Sahaja Yoga here.

07:46.820 --> 07:48.820
As they are built for you especially too

07:48.940 --> 07:52.360
was made with great care about from that they thought

07:52.820 --> 07:55.820
that it was finished and worked very hard.

07:56.030 --> 07:59.780
Day and night, just to prepare this hall for you.

08:01.110 --> 08:03.150
So this is how it is going to work out,

08:03.360 --> 08:05.820
and last time I told them that you should not make

08:06.070 --> 08:09.360
an alcohol out of these molasses

08:09.480 --> 08:11.900
[??] and sell it at the market at a cheap rate,

08:12.150 --> 08:14.280
but make something useful.

08:14.480 --> 08:15.940
So they are trying to find out

08:16.110 --> 08:18.230
a technique about which I talked to them now.

08:18.480 --> 08:21.480
So they are very religious people also.

08:21.980 --> 08:24.110
And they are trying to improve the lot of the people,

08:24.320 --> 08:29.480
by removing all these addictions among the people.

08:31.480 --> 08:34.480
So that is the significance of Rahuri-Puja

08:35.070 --> 08:37.860
and that’s what it is, that you are like Shalivahanas

08:38.110 --> 08:43.440
who are worshipping the Mother and Her shawl.

08:44.320 --> 08:47.480
So today’s Puja has a special significance

08:48.230 --> 08:52.480
– that’s why Rahuri we have very good Sahaja Yogis here,

08:53.110 --> 08:58.940
very developed, very evolved, moral people.

08:59.940 --> 09:02.400
They are not scholars of Sanskrit,

09:02.820 --> 09:05.940
but they are scholars of Sahaja Yoga.

09:06.400 --> 09:10.980
There is a difference between being a scholar of Sanskrit

09:11.230 --> 09:13.320
and a scholar of Sahaja Yoga.

09:15.070 --> 09:20.030
Now for you people I hope it has been a comfortable

09:20.400 --> 09:25.360
stay for you here and

09:27.070 --> 09:32.230
we hope also for the future you are going to enjoy

09:32.940 --> 09:37.820
your journey and enjoy the bliss of the Divine!

09:39.030 --> 09:46.360
[Shri Mataji talks in Marathi]

10:12.440 --> 10:14.320
We don’t read about Rahul`s killing,

10:14.480 --> 10:17.110
because it is Mahalakshmi who killed,

10:17.440 --> 10:21.480
but what we read in the Devi-Mahatmya is the Mahakali`s powers.

10:21.900 --> 10:25.820
But Rahul was killed here in Rahuri by Mahalakshmi,

10:26.480 --> 10:31.110
and that Mahalakshmi power is called as Hrim power,

10:31.480 --> 10:33.280
so that’s why this is Rahu-ri.

10:33.440 --> 10:39.030
Actually it is Rahu-hrim we can say it is Rahu-ri to make it simple.

10:40.110 --> 10:43.480
[Shri Mataji talks in Marathi]

11:24.820 --> 11:26.780
And according to that calendar only

11:26.940 --> 11:29.480
all the Maharashtrians are living,

11:29.980 --> 11:34.440
which is very, I should say, much more subtler than vikram,

11:34.940 --> 11:37.400
this thing. Because in the [INDIST.SOUNDS LIKE: vikram-panjaga]

11:37.860 --> 11:41.780
this area is still called as Kali-Yuga, Kali-Yuga,

11:42.030 --> 11:45.360
but in this [INDIST: SOUNDS LIKE: panjaga; Then: Shalivahana-Panjaga]

11:45.780 --> 11:48.190
it is called as Krita-Yuga. It’s much subtler.

11:48.360 --> 11:52.440
That’s a very wider thing

11:52.820 --> 11:56.820
and it doesn’t give you the different sections

11:57.150 --> 12:00.110
of Kali-Yuga, that how it becomes Krita-Yuga

12:00.280 --> 12:03.320
and ultimately a Satya-Yuga.

12:03.480 --> 12:10.480
The calendar that was used by the North Indians

12:11.030 --> 12:14.480
was the Vikram, and the South Indians used the Shalivahana,

12:14.900 --> 12:19.360
but especially in Maharashtra. But the support came mainly from

12:19.780 --> 12:24.110
[INDIST.] direct, who said that this is the better [INDIST.SOUNDS LIKE: panjaga]

12:24.400 --> 12:30.400
because it deals with subtler side of time.

12:31.070 --> 12:32.440
Subtler side of time.

12:32.900 --> 12:36.480
And that’s why it was regarded as a greater thing.

12:36.940 --> 12:42.230
Now on the first day of

12:42.480 --> 12:47.230
this calendar they put a kalasha

12:47.820 --> 12:53.820
[? A pot] with a shawl as a banner, a kalasha and a shawl as a banner.

12:54.280 --> 13:00.110
That’s why kalash, which is the Kundalini, is the Aquarius.

13:02.820 --> 14:24.860
[Shri Mataji talks in Marathi]

14:25.820 --> 14:28.480
In the older days all the Maharashtrian women used to have

14:28.900 --> 14:34.480
some sort of an additional cloth, a shawl, which they used to carry.

14:35.280 --> 14:38.440
If it was a marriage then they used to have a marriage sari,

14:38.820 --> 14:40.480
[INDIST.SOUNDS LIKE: completed with that shawl].

14:41.110 --> 14:45.070
All the time they had to wear something, a covering over the sari.

14:45.280 --> 14:48.230
Sari was not the end-cloth but now we have become modern,

14:48.440 --> 14:53.480
so we don’t use the, that, another cloth which one has to use.

14:54.110 --> 14:56.480
So, but this is only the custom.

14:56.900 --> 15:00.030
In India is not the point, it is not only in Maharashtra, everywhere.

15:00.280 --> 15:02.480
But there, because a dress was not a sari,

15:02.940 --> 15:05.900
but those who bore the sari did not use, in the North.

15:06.150 --> 15:10.150
But here those who use the sari also use the shawl, on top of that.

15:10.440 --> 15:13.400
And that’s why, you see, this country has a speciality,

15:13.480 --> 15:16.900
this part that they always had this shawl,

15:17.070 --> 15:20.110
whether they went out, for their protection,

15:20.230 --> 15:21.480
or they went for a marriage

15:21.900 --> 15:24.940
or anything they used to have another thing on top.

15:25.230 --> 15:28.230
Now of course we have, symbolically, something modernized.

15:28.360 --> 15:31.110
This is, wearing little pieces to be used as shawls.

15:31.280 --> 15:34.230
You see, everything is getting modernized.

15:35.280 --> 16:12.480
